<HEADLINE> Chinese Congratulation For Thabo Mbeki Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 8 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Government
congratulates South Africa's African National Congress (ANC) for
its success in the general election on June 2 and the presidency
of Thabo Mbeki, Foreign Ministry Spokesperson Zhang Qiyue said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki has been working for friendship with China for a long
time and is an old friend of China, the Foreign Ministry
spokesperson said.
</P>
<P>
Since the two countries established diplomatic relations in
1998, they have had smooth progress in exchanges and cooperation
in politics, economy, culture and other fields, Zhang said, adding
that the Chinese side is convinced that after Mbeki assumes the
office of president, friendly relations and cooperation between
the two will continue to be strengthened and will see new
development through joint efforts. 
</P>
